         <abstract>
            <p>This paper presents an empirical model which is specified to describe the pricing of new convertible bonds. The model is specified as a two-equation simultaneous system where underwriting spread and offering yield are the endogenous variables. The results of the estimation procedure indicate that there is a one-way relationship between underwriting spread and offering yield. Specifically, offering yield has an inverse impact upon underwriting spread, while there is no evidence that underwriting spread influences offering yield.</p>
         </abstract>
